1
00:01:25,539 --> 00:01:29,890
[Coroner's Diary]

2
00:01:30,670 --> 00:01:33,950
[Episode 26]

3
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:45,509
I think

4
00:01:46,509 --> 00:01:48,590
Li Muyun may have figured out who I am.

5
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:52,310
There's a tactic in warfare called
"startling the snake by striking the grass."

6
00:01:52,310 --> 00:01:53,910
He has never seen you before.

7
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:56,039
Even if he grew suspicious
during the autopsy,

8
00:01:56,039 --> 00:01:57,350
he has no proof.

9
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,250
But if you really react,

10
00:01:59,509 --> 00:02:00,970
you'll fall into his trap.

11
00:02:01,420 --> 00:02:03,530
I nearly ruined everything
over something so small.

12
00:02:03,530 --> 00:02:05,090
I still lack patience.

13
00:02:07,530 --> 00:02:09,260
You've done very well already.

14
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:10,530
If it were me,

15
00:02:11,140 --> 00:02:14,199
I might've killed him
on impulse and caused a disaster.

16
00:02:14,530 --> 00:02:15,740
You wouldn't.

17
00:02:16,460 --> 00:02:18,690
You're the most cautious person I know.

18
00:02:19,090 --> 00:02:21,750
You never do anything
you're not certain about.

19
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:24,340
But since returning to the capital,

20
00:02:24,690 --> 00:02:26,950
I'm facing more and more uncertainties.

21
00:02:27,530 --> 00:02:28,860
Because of your father?

22
00:02:32,570 --> 00:02:33,770
He won't listen to me.

23
00:02:34,460 --> 00:02:35,590
How can I be certain?

24
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:39,060
What worries me now

25
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:40,990
is Prince Jin and Lord Shen's case.

26
00:02:41,570 --> 00:02:43,310
I went to the Ministry of Justice
to find the files,

27
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:44,910
but they've all been sealed.

28
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:46,579
It seems this matter

29
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:49,140
is far more complicated than we imagined.

30
00:02:49,410 --> 00:02:50,180
Today, when I saw

31
00:02:50,180 --> 00:02:52,250
Li Muyun mention my father,

32
00:02:54,570 --> 00:02:56,090
he showed no guilt at all.

33
00:02:56,570 --> 00:02:58,340
I thought he was shameless,

34
00:02:58,340 --> 00:02:59,530
and I was furious.

35
00:03:00,220 --> 00:03:01,820
But now that I think about it,

36
00:03:02,110 --> 00:03:03,970
what if he really has nothing
to be ashamed of?

37
00:03:03,970 --> 00:03:06,320
What if he really just did
what he was supposed to do?

38
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,450
What if my father...

39
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:11,530
really did help Prince Jin...

40
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:15,570
Wan,

41
00:03:16,460 --> 00:03:17,900
stop overthinking it.

42
00:03:19,850 --> 00:03:21,050
We've just returned.

43
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:25,370
We need to establish ourselves
in the Ministry of Justice before we can act.

44
00:03:25,370 --> 00:03:26,130
Trust me—

45
00:03:27,530 --> 00:03:29,780
the truth will come out sooner or later.

46
00:03:30,740 --> 00:03:31,940
We'll uncover it,

47
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:33,410
step

48
00:03:33,810 --> 00:03:34,810
by step.

49
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:39,690
Prince Sui can speak now.

50
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:42,310
Once his mind is more settled,

51
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:44,130
I'll ask if he

52
00:03:44,130 --> 00:03:46,329
remembers anything about Consort Jin.

53
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:47,500
Alright.

54
00:03:48,690 --> 00:03:50,950
Don't think about these things anymore.

55
00:03:51,090 --> 00:03:54,220
You've worked hard these days.
You should get some rest.

56
00:03:54,340 --> 00:03:56,060
The Ministry of Justice prison

57
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:58,990
isn't exactly a comfortable place
for questioning.

58
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:11,970
Come on, Your Highness!

59
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:14,620
Come on! Where are you?

60
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:15,740
The show is going to begin!

61
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:16,740
Over here!

62
00:04:17,940 --> 00:04:18,850
Over here?

63
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:20,020
I got you!

64
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:21,060
I'm too tired to play.

65
00:04:21,060 --> 00:04:22,300
You guys catch me now.

66
00:04:22,660 --> 00:04:24,180
Coming, Sir.

67
00:04:25,829 --> 00:04:27,270
It feels good.

68
00:04:27,450 --> 00:04:29,210
Give my shoulders a massage.

69
00:04:36,060 --> 00:04:37,140
What's going on?

70
00:04:37,170 --> 00:04:39,030
Weren't you supposed to catch me?

71
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:44,830
What are you doing here?

72
00:04:46,570 --> 00:04:47,659
Why are you crying?

73
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:50,080
Which bastard bullied you?

74
00:04:50,420 --> 00:04:52,020
I'll take him down right now!

75
00:04:56,770 --> 00:05:00,060
It was you, you bastard!

76
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,880
I thought you were dead.

77
00:05:07,210 --> 00:05:08,800
How could I be dead?

78
00:05:09,110 --> 00:05:09,920
The other day,

79
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:12,880
someone was killed at Fengqi House.

80
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:15,690
It was a brutal death!

81
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:18,540
So,

82
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,040
you thought it was me?

83
00:05:22,540 --> 00:05:24,670
I've been looking everywhere for you.

84
00:05:24,790 --> 00:05:27,670
I went to Fengqi House
and Prince Yi's Mansion

85
00:05:28,130 --> 00:05:30,250
but couldn't find you.

86
00:05:30,860 --> 00:05:33,060
I heard Chi was investigating the case,

87
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:35,400
so I rushed over.

88
00:05:35,810 --> 00:05:36,860
It turned out

89
00:05:37,690 --> 00:05:40,090
Little Wan'er was performing the autopsy.

90
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:43,430
The body really looked a lot like you.

91
00:05:45,010 --> 00:05:46,620
It really looked like you.

92
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:48,540
Even if it wasn't you,

93
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:49,330
the officer said

94
00:05:49,330 --> 00:05:51,659
the deceased spent every day in brothels.

95
00:05:51,659 --> 00:05:52,890
What if...

96
00:05:52,890 --> 00:05:55,450
the next one is you?

97
00:05:56,860 --> 00:05:59,620
What if you really died?

98
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:02,740
What am I supposed to do?

99
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:10,810
If I really die,

100
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:13,420
I'll make sure you

101
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:17,000
stand at the front
of my funeral procession.

102
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:21,300
Fine.

103
00:06:21,940 --> 00:06:23,770
I won't just stand at the front—

104
00:06:23,770 --> 00:06:25,890
I'll perform the rites for you,

105
00:06:25,890 --> 00:06:26,620
alright?

106
